## Phase 15: Appointment Logic Refinements
- [x] Fix "Bad state" error on successful appointment booking caused by parsing `expand['patient']` when linking isn't immediate.
- [x] Auto-select doctor in [CreateAppointmentScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart#15-24) if the clinic only has one doctor attached.
- [x] Restrict Walk-in appointment creation to the current date only (preventing future walk-ins and fixing the In-Progress logic gap).
- [x] Auto-create Patient records on Walk-In submission so they correctly populate the Patients List tab.
- [x] Fix endless loading bug in [AvailableSlotsScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/scheduling/screens/available_slots_screen.dart#12-34) for today's date by wrapping the initial load in a post-frame callback.
- [x] Update Date Slider in [AppointmentListScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart#11-18) to generate a 31-day window strictly centered around the selected date's yesterday, and dynamically rebuild and animate the scroll position when a new calendar date is picked.
- [x] Expand [CreateAppointmentScreen](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/create_appointment_screen.dart#15-24) and `appointment_provider` to embed the full patient details form (DOB, Address, Emergency Contact, Allergies) natively into the Walk-In appointment booking flow, completely eliminating the need for a secondary registration step.
